## 9. Chrome Extension Components

### 9.1 Manifest

Use Manifest V3.

Required concepts:

```txt
content_scripts
service_worker
permissions
host_permissions
action popup
```

Chrome content scripts are used to run JavaScript on pages matching configured URL patterns. ([Chrome for Developers](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/extensions/reference/manifest/content-scripts?utm_source=chatgpt.com "Manifest - content scripts | Chrome Extensions"))

Background logic should use MV3 service worker because MV3 replaces persistent background pages with service workers. ([Chrome for Developers](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/extensions/develop/migrate/to-service-workers?utm_source=chatgpt.com "Migrate to a service worker - Chrome for Developers"))

### 9.2 Content Script

Responsibility:

```txt
Read DOM
Extract messages
Extract images
Normalize content
Send extracted data to popup/service worker
```

Content script should be injected on:

```txt
https://chatgpt.com/*
https://chat.openai.com/*
```

### 9.3 Popup

Responsibility:

```txt
Show export button
Show progress
Show validation status
Trigger export
```

Minimal UI:

```txt
[Export Current Chat]

Status:
Ready / Extracting / Downloading assets / Creating ZIP / Done / Failed
```

### 9.4 Service Worker

Responsibility:

```txt
Coordinate messages
Use Chrome downloads API
Handle final ZIP download
```

The `chrome.downloads` API can programmatically start and manage downloads, but the extension must declare the `"downloads"` permission. ([Chrome for Developers](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/extensions/reference/api/downloads?utm_source=chatgpt.com "chrome.downloads | API - Chrome for Developers"))

