## 15. DOM Extraction Strategy

Do not rely only on fragile selectors like:

```css
div:nth-child(4)
```

Use layered detection.

Recommended priority:

```txt
1. semantic attributes / data-testid if available
2. message role labels
3. repeated message container patterns
4. content structure
5. fallback visible text extraction
```

The DOM will change over time, so the extractor should be modular.

Suggested files:

```txt
extractConversation.ts
extractMessage.ts
extractBlocks.ts
domUtils.ts
```

### Important

The extension should not depend on one single selector.

Use a strategy list:

```ts
const messageContainerStrategies = [
  findByDataTestId,
  findByArticleNodes,
  findByConversationTurnPattern,
  findByFallbackTextBlocks
];
```

---

## 16. Extraction Rules

### 16.1 Text

Preserve paragraphs and line breaks.

### 16.2 Code

Preserve fenced code blocks.

Example:

```md
```ts
const hello = "world";
```

```

If language cannot be detected, use plain fence:

```md
```

code

```

```

### 16.3 Tables

If table exists as DOM table, convert to Markdown table.

### 16.4 Lists

Preserve:

```md
- item
- item
```

and:

```md
1. item
2. item
```

### 16.5 Images

Insert image where it appears in the message.

```md
![](assets/001.png)
```

### 16.6 Math

If math is visible as text/LaTeX, preserve as text.

MVP does not need perfect math reconstruction.

---

## 17. Validation Requirements

After extraction, validate:

```txt
conversation has title
conversation has at least one message
messages are ordered
markdown is not empty
asset references exist in ZIP
code blocks are not empty
image references match assets
```

If validation fails, show warning in popup.

Do not silently fail.

---

## 18. Error Handling

Common failures:

```txt
Not on ChatGPT page
No conversation found
Message parsing failed
Image download failed
ZIP generation failed
Download permission missing
```

Popup should show practical messages:

```txt
Not a supported ChatGPT conversation page.
Could not detect messages.
Export completed with 2 asset warnings.
```

